Журналисты везде одинаковы

<blockquote cite="http://www.ubuntuvibes.com/2012/04/linus-torvalds-appreciates-ubuntus-user.html" style="border-left: 5px solid #EEEEEE; margin-bottom: 18px; padding-left: 15px; color: #888;">_TechCrunch:_ I really think that Ubuntu has generally had the right approach, and been very user-centric.

_Linus Torvalds:_ The same thing is what frustrated me about many of the changes in Gnome 3. The whole “let’s make it clutter-free” was taken to the point where it was actually hard to get things done, and it wasn’t even obvious *how* to do things when you could do them. That kind of minimalist approach is not forward progress, it’s just UI people telling people “we know better”, even if it makes things harder to do. That kind of “things that used to be easy are suddenly hard or impossible” just drives me up the wall, and frustrates me.
<small style="color: #BFBFBF; display: block; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 18px;">— [http://www.ubuntuvibes.com/2012/04/linus-torvalds-appreciates-ubuntus-user.html](http://www.ubuntuvibes.com/2012/04/linus-torvalds-appreciates-ubuntus-user.html)</small></blockquote>  
Это фрагмент интервью Торвальдса — TechCrunch′у, по случаю вручения Линусу премии [Millenium Technology Prize](http://www.technologyacademy.fi/millennium-technology-prize/). Краткий перевод фрагмента:  
— Правда ли, что подход Убунту очень правильный?  
— Да я на стену лезу, когда сталкиваюсь с таким подходом.

Перепечатка интервью на _Ubuntu_Vibes (ссылка дана на нее) озаглавлена как? — Правильно: «Linus Torvalds Appreciates Ubuntu's User Centric Approach».

В оригинальном интервью еще про русского интервьюера смешно.
